main event: Multiple military and civilian sources reported seeing four unidentified flying objects (UFOs) over Panama City, Florida and Tyndall Air Force Base on 28th October 1956.
interesting points: The objects were described as cigar-shaped, pea-shaped, and egg-shaped, with changing appearances at times.
They were observed moving irregularly, converging into a diamond formation, and then disappearing beyond the horizon.
The report includes ground visual observations with no conclusive explanation for the sightings.
The objects were compared to car headlights moving back and forth and were observed to move with high speeds.
Despite the detailed observations, there was insufficient data for a conclusive evaluation of the objects.
location: Panama City, Florida and Tyndall Air Force Base, Florida
